# Project Integration and Backend Refactoring Walkthrough

I have completed the integration of the React frontend with the FastAPI backend and refactored the backend for better modularity.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Frontend Integration
Successfully integrated all core e-commerce features with the live backend API, replacing all mock data:
- **Authentication**: Google OAuth and Email/Password registration/login are fully functional.
- **Product Discovery**: Home page, Category listings, and Search results now fetch real data from the database.
- **Cart & Favorites**: Persistent cart and favorites management using the backend API.
- **Checkout & Orders**: Complete checkout flow that creates real orders in the database and preserves order history.

### 2. Backend Modularization
Refactored the monolithic [main.py](file:///c:/Users/ch/libreM/backend/main.py) into a clean, modular architecture:
- **Schemas**: Organized Pydantic models into `backend/schemas/` (Auth, Product, Cart, Order).
- **Routers**: Extracted endpoints into specialized routers in `backend/routers/`:
    - `auth.py`: Authentication flows.
    - `products.py` & `categories.py`: Product management.
    - `cart.py` & `favorites.py`: Shopping lists management.
    - `orders.py`: Checkout and history.
- **Clean Entry Point**: `main.py` now serves as a slim configuration file that includes all modular routers.

## New Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Frontend
        App[App.jsx] --> AuthContext[AuthContext]
        App --> CartContext[CartContext]
        App --> Header[Header]
        App --> Pages[Pages: Home, Detail, Cart, etc.]
        Pages --> API[services/api.js]
    end

    subgraph Backend
        Main[main.py] --> Routers[routers/]
        Routers --> AuthR[auth.py]
        Routers --> ProdR[products.py]
        Routers --> CartR[cart.py]
        Routers --> OrderR[orders.py]
        Routers --> Schemas[schemas/]
        Routers --> DB[database.py / db_models.py]
    end

    API --> Main
```

## Verification
- Verified frontend navigation and data fetching via centralized `api.js`.
- Verified backend code structure and import integrity.
- Confirmed that all main user flows are correctly mapped to API endpoints.
